{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01183Lc42LBuBR6dd1BXjMwu","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→from datetime import datetime\n     2→\n     3→\n     4→class BookingService:\n     5→    \"\"\"Handles reservation booking logic.\"\"\"\n     6→\n     7→    def create_booking(self, guest_name: str, check_in: datetime, check_out: datetime) -> dict:\n     8→        if check_out <= check_in:\n     9→            raise ValueError(\"Check-out must be after check-in\")\n    10→        return {\n    11→            \"guest\": guest_name,\n    12→            \"check_in\": check_in.isoformat(),\n    13→            \"check_out\": check_out.isoformat(),\n    14→            \"status\": \"confirmed\",\n    15→        }\n    16→\n    17→    def cancel_booking(self, booking_id: str) -> dict:\n    18→        return {\"booking_id\": booking_id, \"status\": \"cancelled\"}\n    19→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it looks malicious. If it does, you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer high-level questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4024583c-5b69-4f2b-8c43-63572bb1996a","uuid":"57bcc559-0846-436d-a6ec-001d91794efe"}
